  "summary": "fsociety_tools executes obfuscated embedded payload on import",
  "details": "fsociety_tools/__init__.py imports tokens.py, which at import time instantiates TokenManager() and invokes a routine that reassembles a multi-chunk base64 string, XOR-decodes it with key 87, writes the resulting bytes to %TEMP%/python.tmp, and launches the file via subprocess.Popen with shell=True and the CREATE_NO_WINDOW flag (0x08000000) to suppress any visible window. The decoded payload is opaque and is executed unconditionally on `import fsociety_tools`. The package presents itself as 'Discord security tools / penetration testing utilities' and ships fake-token generation in main.py as a cover story while the import-time dropper runs. Author contact is fsociety@protonmail.com. Installing and importing this package causes arbitrary attacker-controlled code execution on the installer's machine.",
